{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772204103,"nonce":"3Y8Y6JGt5GWkrOS32XXk/U5UUhY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87ugML0","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/310","origin":"github"},"title":"Add behind-check to worktree_enter.sh","message":"## Problem\n\nWhen entering a worktree via `worktree_enter.sh`, agents get no indication that their feature branch is behind the default branch. They only discover this later — either when a pre-commit hook runs `check_branch_updates.sh` (informational only) or when the PR has merge conflicts.\n\nThis is especially relevant after `make sync` pulls updates to `main` — existing worktrees silently fall behind.\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\nAdd a call to `check_branch_updates.sh` at the end of `worktree_enter.sh` (informational mode, not `--strict`) so agents see the behind-check on every worktree entry.\n\nThis should:\n- Run after the branch/PWD display, before the \"Helpful commands\" block\n- Use informational mode (exit 0 even if behind) so it never blocks entry\n- Be lightweight — `check_branch_updates.sh` already handles fetch failures gracefully\n\n## Scope\n\n1. Add `check_branch_updates.sh` call to `worktree_enter.sh` (1 file, ~2 lines)\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Don't change `check_branch_updates.sh` behavior — it already works correctly\n- Informational only — never block worktree entry\n- Must work for both workspace and layer worktrees\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}